        <div id="off_help" class="tooltip">
          <b>Off</b> - Folding is disabled.
        </div>
        <div id="idle_light_help" class="tooltip">
          <b>Idle Light</b> - Your computer will only fold when it has been
          idle long enough for the Folding@home screensaver to become active.
          Even then it will operate at a reduced level.  This setting can be
          useful for laptops which have problems with overheating or fan
          noise.
        </div>
        <div id="idle_help" class="tooltip">
          <b>Idle</b> - Your computer will only fold when it has been idle
          long enough for the Folding@home screensaver to become active.
        </div>
        <div id="light_help" class="tooltip">
          <b>Light</b> - Recommended for laptops this setting will minimize
          the impact of Folding@home at the cost of lower performance.
        </div>
        <div id="medium_help" class="tooltip">
          <b>Medium</b> - A higher performance setting recommended for most
          users.
        </div>
        <div id="full_help" class="tooltip">
          <b>Full</b> - Contribute as much as possible.  Warning, this
          setting may cause some machines to get hot or the fan to run very
          hard. If this is a problem simply move this slider to a lower
          setting.
        </div>

